{"about_the_game":"This game takes place in the world of dreams, It features an American officer of Iraqi descent who participated in the 2003 invasion of Iraq, This officer was involved in black operations, In 2006 he decided to expose these operations because they had killed some civilians for political reasons, He stole sensitive documents with the intention of leaking them to the press, After an attempt to arrest him, he committed suicide, and the documents were never found, His brain was preserved for years, In 2012, there was a secret program to penetrate minds, His brain was connected to computers, and an officer was summoned to undertake a journey inside his mind to find where he hid the secret files, ensuring they are never published or fall into the wrong hands.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe game is similar to:<br />\r\n1- The Evil Within: The mind machine and how to enter the mind. <br />\r\n2- Resident Evil: Puzzles and the environment. <br />\r\n3- Metro Exodus: radiation, underground tunnels, and some weapons.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n* the game stands out as it doesn't imitate any other game; all its ideas are original. <br />\r\n* It features AI assistance integrated with the main character, set within an ancient fantasy world. <br />\r\n* The graphics are stunning, delivering excellent visual performance. <br />\r\n* the game avoids repetition; as players progress, they encounter new challenges and enemies. <br />\r\n* Notably, the game breaks the fourth wall, engaging directly with players and connecting the virtual world with reality.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhat feeling will you be left with after experiencing this game?\tTrying something new that you haven't tried before, it's like playing one of Hideo Kojima's games for the first time.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nImportant note: The game is an incomplete early access version, meaning it does not offer a complete story mode. If you buy the early access version, you will enjoy an early experience and you will save your money because you will get the full release as soon as it is released and for free. You will also be supporting the development efforts.","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2517220/page_bg_generated_v6b.jpg?t=1720819932","background_raw":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2517220/page.bg.jpg?t=1720819932","capsule_image":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2517220/capsule_231x87.jpg?t=1720819932","capsule_imagev5":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2517220/capsule_184x69.jpg?t=1720819932","categories":[{"description":"Single-player","id":2},{"description":"Family Sharing","id":62}],"content_descriptors":{"ids":[],"notes":null},"detailed_description":"This game takes place in the world of dreams, It features an American officer of Iraqi descent who participated in the 2003 invasion of Iraq, This officer was involved in black operations, In 2006 he decided to expose these operations because they had killed some civilians for political reasons, He stole sensitive documents with the intention of leaking them to the press, After an attempt to arrest him, he committed suicide, and the documents were never found, His brain was preserved for years, In 2012, there was a secret program to penetrate minds, His brain was connected to computers, and an officer was summoned to undertake a journey inside his mind to find where he hid the secret files, ensuring they are never published or fall into the wrong hands.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe game is similar to:<br />\r\n1- The Evil Within: The mind machine and how to enter the mind. <br />\r\n2- Resident Evil: Puzzles and the environment. <br />\r\n3- Metro Exodus: radiation, underground tunnels, and some weapons.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n* the game stands out as it doesn't imitate any other game; all its ideas are original. <br />\r\n* It features AI assistance integrated with the main character, set w